HEADWORD: malta fever
<hw>malta fever</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>An infectious
disease contracted from meat or milk products from infected domestic
animals; called also <altname>brucellosis</altname> and
<altname>undulant fever</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
